7LAG
A person who signs his or her name to a loan agreement, lease or credit application. If the primary debtor does not pay, the cosigner is fully responsible for the loan or debt.
Many people use cosigners to qualify for a loan or credit card. Landlords may require a cosigner when renting to a student or someone with a poor credit history.

07”Are you absolutely certain you’re ready to perform the memorial flight?”
07“Yes. I’ve made my decision on that particular matter. Please quit bringing this up. You will not get things your way no matter how much you beg – you should know as much by now.”
07“So I see… By the way, are we being overheard? This conversation is to be kept purely confidential – I need to be sure we are not.”
07“Don’t worry Emilie, I assure you that my darling Hawkilara is asleep and Hawkins was invited to spend the might elsewhere. Carry on, please.”
07The hushed sound of two female voices carried over to where a little bird lay, tucked snugly under a carpet made from downy feathers. It was midnight and she was supposed to be resting, yet she could not sleep for reasons unknown. Her eyes fluttered open as she heard her name, and she blinked in an attempt to clear her mind, feathers ruffling and fluffing up once she’d settled into a comfier position.
07This was her mum and an acquaintance of hers conversing; they perched atop a rock not far from the nest and sat there whilst discussing matters which weren’t meant for her ears. However, her curiosity was ignited and the temptation to listen in became irresistible. So she lay there, keeping perfectly still in order to maintain the illusion of sleep, and unaware as they were, the two adults kept talking.
07o3o
07The other female gave a mirthless laugh in reply.
12o.o
2XD
07“A solo mating flight to honour the memory of the bird I love, taking a new mate for the sake of the community and biding farewell with my offspring permanently. I can’t believe you’re trying to boss me around, believing I am this weak and easily swayed.”
07Emilie was stunned into silence. Clearly, the fierceness took her by surprise. An awkward silence fell between the two until Emilie attempted to get back on topic.
07“Hawkilara is leaving the nest soon, then? And who are you taking as your new mate?”
07And in the nest, tucked under her carpet of warm, downy feathers, lay a broken-hearted Hawkilara, feeling as though her life was in shambles.

12SPARKLES WTF.
“Humans sun burn due to the scorching of living cells in our system.
